OL,3,C'I was blamed for my baby's death':
OL,4,CMums speak out on maternity care
OL,6,F"We were fighting to try and say, no,
OL,7,Fthis happened to us, and what happened
OL,8,Fwasn't right. It wasn't fair. And no
OL,9,Fone was listening."
OL,11,FShe added: "It shouldn't be down to
OL,12,Ffamilies to have to stand up and fight
OL,13,Fafter going through so much. They
OL,14,Fshould be recognising this themselves.
OL,16,F"The government should be recognising
OL,17,Fit. The hospitals should be looking at
OL,18,Ftheir own patterns.
