OL,3,C'I was blamed for my baby's death':
OL,4,CMums speak out on maternity care
OL,6,F"People need to make change otherwise
OL,7,Fthis is just going to keep happening,
OL,8,Fand the number of bereaved families -
OL,9,Fmums, dads and parents across the
OL,10,Fcountry - are just going to keep
OL,11,Fgrowing, and continuing to fight until
OL,12,Fit's just too much."
OL,14,FShrewbury & Telford Hospital Trust has
OL,15,Fapologised to Katie and Neil, with
OL,16,Fchief executive Louise Barnett
OL,17,Facknowledging it was due to failings
OL,18,Fin care.
